    "and g * denotes the number of relativistic degrees of freedom.",
    "If a large lepton asymmetry and/or primordial magnetic fields were present in the early Universe, the QCD phase transition might have been of first order (Schwarz & Stuke 2009; Wygas et al. 2018; Middeldorf-Wygas et al. 2022; Vovchenko et al. 2021; Cao 2023).",
    "In this case, one would expect additional sources of GWs, from the collision of broken phase bubbles and the subsequent development of sound waves in the primordial fluid (Kosowsky et al. 1992; Kosowsky & Turner 1993; Caprini et al. 2008; Huber & Konstandin 2008; Jinno & Takimoto 2017; Cutting et al. 2018; Hindmarsh et al. 2014 Hindmarsh et al., 2015 Hindmarsh et al., 2017)).",
    "This was analysed for PTAs, e.g.",
